<TITLE> Crash snaps Dhaka-Ctg rail link </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Feni, July 23 (bdnews24.com)--The rail link between Dhaka and Chittagong has remained snapped since early on Thursday after a passenger train crashed into loaded truck stuck at the Fatehpur level crossing on the Dhaka-Chittagong highway in Feni. It might take unti evening to restore the rail communication, Feni assistant railway station master Mohammed Harun told bdnews24.com. Ten people were injured in the incident. Harun said the engine of the truck carrying iron coil stopped while negotiating the level crossing at around 5am. Chittagong-bound express train Turna-Nishitha hit it, causing three of its compartments to bounce off the track. The injured were admitted to local clinics, he added. A rescue train arrived at the scene of the accident from Chittagong at around 9am. A police team led by assistant superintendent of police Shakila Sultana is overseeing the rescue operation, the railway official said. The train was removed from the level crossing after 7am. But vehicles were using one side of the level crossing as the engine of the train was left on the spot. Road transport on the Dhaka-Chittagong highway was also halted due to the accident. Traffic was diverted to Feni town for taking the highway. bdnews
